title: High school roundup: Forks, Elmira pitch shutouts
text:
High school roundup: Forks, Elmira pitch shutouts 
By wbng sports October 13, 2015 Updated Oct 13, 2015 at 11:58 PM EDT 
(WBNG Binghamton) The STAC girl's soccer semifinals are set, and they involve four teams all ranked top eight in the state in their respective classes. A few of those teams were in action on Tuesday. 
Elmira, the sixth ranked team in Class AA, shut out Union-Endicott 3-0 on the road. The Express got two goals from Kendra Oldroyd on their way to the win. 
Meanwhile, Chenango Forks also pitched a shutout. The Blue Devils took care of rival Chenango Valley at home. Forks entered the week ranked eighth in the state in Class B. 
The other STAC semifinal this weekend will be between Vestal and Seton. 
Owego sweeps JC Owego earned a clean sweep of Johnson City in girl's volleyball on Tuesday evening. The Indians won 25-16, 25-5 and 25-8 to win in straight sets. 
Vestal captures STAC golf title Led by a 75 from Nick Barney, Vestal won the STAC golf title on Tuesday at Cornell's Robert Trent Jones Golf Course. 
The Golden Bears shot a collective 393. Corning finished in second place with a 412.
